Definition.WordDefinition:
Auburn \Au"burn\, a. [OE. auburne blonde, OF. alborne, auborne, fr. LL. alburnus whitish, fr. L. albus white. Cf. {Alburn}.] 1. Flaxen-colored. [Obs.] --Florio. [1913 Webster]
2. Reddish brown. [1913 Webster]
His auburn locks on either shoulder flowed. --Dryden. [1913 Webster] ||
auburn adj : (of hair) colored a moderate brown; "auburn hair" [syn: {reddish-brown}]
